node.text:
The teep is one of the most thrown techniques in Muay Thai. Just like the jab in boxing, the teep is used to set up techniques and used as both an attack and defence. 🖊 

In this video I show you common mistakes I see when people are throwing this technique and how to correct them to throw a teep like a pro. 🙌🏼

node.title: How To Teep Like A Pro With @ellisbarboza

As a beginner it is very important that you perfect this from day one so the rest of your game can improve easily.

node.text:
Perfecting the CROSS with pro Muay Thai fighter and coach @fab_delannon 🥊 
-
Some pointers for throwing a strong corss👇
1. Rotate the rear foot like you are crushing a cigarette
2. Position yourself as if you’re getting ready to sprint. This will help you put the full weight of your body behind the punch!
3. Knees are bent, maintain your center of gravity over your hips when striking
4. Avoid flaring the elbow when retracting. Punch “down the pipe”
------------------
Follow @muaythaimagic for 
Training Tips • Mindset • Nutrition • Motivation - Link in bio. 
-
#MuayThaiMagic #TheHomeOfMuayThai
------------------
